## 2. Health Check Commands

### Quick Check
```bash
# HTTP health probe
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 http://localhost:{{ port }}{{ health_path | default(value="/health") }}
# Expected: 200
```

### Full Diagnostic
```bash
# Check process is running
pgrep -f "{{ process_name | default(value=service_name) }}" && echo "RUNNING" || echo "NOT RUNNING"

# Check port is listening
lsof -i :{{ port }} | head -5

# Check recent logs (last 50 lines)
journalctl -u {{ service_name | lower | replace(from=" ", to="-") }} --no-pager -n 50 2>/dev/null || tail -50 /var/log/{{ service_name | lower | replace(from=" ", to="-") }}.log 2>/dev/null

# Check resource usage
ps aux | grep "{{ process_name | default(value=service_name) }}" | grep -v grep | awk '{print "CPU: "$3"% | MEM: "$4"% | PID: "$2}'
```

### Database Check
```bash
# Verify data store connectivity
{{ db_check_command | default(value="# Add database-specific health check here") }}
```

